Ad Text:
CS Energy is seeking a dynamic Head of Trading and Analytics to shape the future of our trading, portfolio optimisation, and analytics functions. This is your opportunity to drive strategy, innovation, and performance in one of Australia’s most dynamic energy markets.

Reporting to the Chief Commercial Officer, the Head of Trading and Analytics will develop and execute trading strategies that maximise value, balance risk and reward, and align with CS Energy’s enterprise strategy and risk appetite. You’ll ensure every decision is grounded in analytical excellence, data integrity, and sound governance.

As a strategic and technical leader, you’ll oversee trading across physical and derivative markets while empowering your team to deliver market intelligence, dynamic forecasting, and forward-looking insights that inform pricing, risk management, and capital allocation across the business.

About you

You’re a proven leader in energy or commodity trading with deep expertise in the National Electricity Market and a sharp ability to interpret market trends, regulatory shifts, and policy settings. You combine commercial acumen with calm, decisive judgement, even under pressure, and you’re unwavering in your commitment to governance and risk discipline.

You’re passionate about building high-performing teams and embedding systems that drive consistency, innovation, and continuous improvement.
Success in this role means ensuring CS Energy’s trading function is insight-driven, future-ready, and aligned with our purpose to power Queensland safely, reliably, and affordably while creating long-term sustainable value.

Why Join Us

This is your opportunity to influence how CS Energy navigates the evolving energy landscape, driving decisions that support a reliable, affordable, and sustainable energy future for Queensland and beyond.

How to apply

On Talent has been engaged to lead this recruitment for CS Energy. To apply please provide your resume and a cover letter outlining your relevant achievements and motivation for this role.

For a confidential discussion, contact Natasha Olsson-Seeto or Jay Baxter at On Talent on (07) 3305 5800.

Applications close: 21 November 2025

Senior Analyst - Financial Modelling

A business that’s shaping the future of investing — and you can be part of that journey.

This is a unique opportunity to work at the heart of a dynamic investment function, supporting complex and diverse investment strategies.

You’ll gain exposure across asset classes, collaborate with experienced professionals, and be part of a high-performing team that values innovation, accountability, and continuous learning.

You will contribute to strategic decision-making, and ensure the smooth running of financial operations through accurate modelling, reporting, and compliance oversight.

This is a high-impact position suited to someone who enjoys problem-solving, has strong financial acumen, and is looking to step into a role with leadership exposure.

Key Responsibilities:
Oversee a portfolio of fund transactions, managing financial and operational workflows.
Build and maintain complex financial models to track asset and investor cashflows, ensuring data is accurate and timely.
Analyse monthly project and fund updates and update internal systems for decision-making purposes.
Coordinate capital calls and investor distributions, ensuring alignment with funding needs and investment timelines.
Process payments and secure appropriate approvals for capital deployment and returns.
Support the production of high-quality monthly and quarterly investor reports.
Qualifications & Experience:

Degree in Finance, Accounting, Commerce, or a related discipline. Postgraduate qualifications (e.g. CFA) 
Minimum 5 years’ experience in financial services, ideally in areas such as investment banking, project finance, or credit/fund operations.
Skills & Attributes:

Advanced Excel and financial modelling skills, with a strong grasp of valuation and cashflow analysis.
Clear communication and presentation abilities, with a focus on concise, stakeholder-friendly reporting.
Strong attention to detail and a proactive approach to identifying and solving problems.
Ability to manage multiple projects and priorities in a dynamic environment.
A collaborative mindset, with proven experience working across teams and functions.
Leadership capability, with experience coaching or supporting junior team members preferred.
Why apply?

This is an exceptional opportunity for a driven professional looking to make a meaningful impact within a supportive, collaborative, and high-performing team.
The firm promotes a culture of integrity, accountability, and respect — where initiative, excellence, and team success are valued.
If you are looking for a role that offers exposure to complex transactions, leadership responsibilities, and career progression, this position offers all that and more.

To be considered for this role, please apply to james@lansonpartners.com

Ad Text:
Here at Investa, we’re all about creating spaces that reflect how people work, live, and thrive today—and how they’ll want to do so in the future. For over 20 years, we’ve led the way in making positive change in Australia’s workplaces. We’re an Australian diversified real estate company with a recognised track-record of investment and development across both office and living markets. Our purpose is to welcome the world to better places. We’re people first and entrepreneurial, with a strong service ethos.  

Why join us? We’ve made it our business to understand how people want to live and work today, tomorrow and beyond and as you’d expect, we practise what we preach in our own workplace as well.​ We’re known for our supportive, inclusive, and flexible work culture. With recognition from the Workplace Gender Equality Agency, the Australian Workplace Equality Index, and multiple awards for workplace flexibility, our people and the way we work together are our difference. 

As our Senior Research Manager, you will play a pivotal role in shaping market insights that drive investor engagement and capital raising. Your critical analysis will influence strategic decisions and elevate the Research team’s reputation through best-practice analytics.


You’re a confident communicator who shines when presenting to senior stakeholders and investors. With a talent for writing and speaking clearly, concisely, and with impact, you bring a commercially minded, ‘investor-first’ approach to every interaction. You thrive on generating fresh research themes and transforming them into compelling content that resonates with investors.

Curiosity fuels your work. You’re passionate about leveraging data to uncover insights and solve complex problems. Analytical thinking and strong problem-solving skills are second nature to you.



Your key responsibilities: 

Prepare and deliver market insights to investors to contribute to ongoing relationship management and capital raising initiatives
Actively challenge current market and business thinking to influence the Investa leadership team and business decision-making process
Provide Research function efficiencies to deliver a best practice service and meet internal customer demands/expectations
Incorporate the Living sector into the current Research processes and deliverables
Support the General Manager, Investor Relations & Research in reshaping the Research function through consultation with key business partners, ensuring it is aligned to the evolving needs of investors and the business
Develop and deliver a content schedule including scheduled reporting and topical pieces to investors subscribed to our Research reports
Advise the business of emerging trends in Australian and global commercial real estate markets
Deliver compelling presentations and tailored briefings to institutional investors (existing and prospective) in our pooled fund and mandate businesses
An ability to turn complex data into clear, actionable stories that inform business decisions.



What you bring: 

Tertiary qualifications in Business, Commerce, Property Economics or similar is required
Experience as a leader or senior team member in a research team or economist setting within Commercial Property is essential
Knowledge of both the Commercial Office and Living sectors highly desirable
Sound knowledge of key vendors in the market ie. Data providers
Understanding of capital transactions and capital raising processes at a high level
A deep understanding of property markets, trends, and key economic drivers
High level of Excel proficiency, including competency in using complex formulas


What we offer: 

Career Development: Leadership programs, education assistance, study support, professional membership fee support 
Lifestyle: We offer generous parental leave, return to work program, and summer hours 
Inclusive Culture: A safe, welcoming environment for all, including individuals from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander communities, the LGBTQ+ community, and those who are neurodivergent 
Flexibility: We do our best to support you to be able to do the things that are important to you. We offer over 21 formal flexible work options, plus a truly supportive approach to balancing work with life’s priorities 
Health and Wellness: Discounted health insurance, free health and wellbeing services, discounted fitness classes, reproductive health benefits  
Financial: Fully funded life and TPD insurance, novated leasing and retail discounts 


We encourage people of all backgrounds to apply. Even if you don’t meet all the criteria, we’d love to hear from you. 

We understand that traditional hiring processes can come with challenges for some people. If you have a disability, identify as gender diverse or are neurodivergent, please reach out to our Recruitment Manager, arockliff@investa.com.au and Amy will tailor our processes to accommodate your specific needs. If you require no additional assistance to accommodate your requirements and wish to be considered for this position, kindly submit your application online. We request that applications not be submitted directly to this email address. 

A note to recruitment agencies:  Investa does not accept unsolicited resumes or candidate profiles from recruitment agencies. We will not be responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes sent direct without prior engagement. Thank you for your understanding.

Our client is a major Australian infrastructure organisation responsible for managing and developing a critical asset. Operating in a multi-stakeholder setting, this business is synonymous with complexity, scale, and strategic importance. Due to ongoing investment and transformation, an opportunity exists for an accomplished Senior Finance Analyst to play a pivotal role in the management of operational expenditure and business performance.

The Role
As Senior Finance Analyst, you will take ownership of Opex reporting and analysis across a diverse portfolio, partnering with operational and corporate stakeholders to drive cost efficiency, transparency, and accountability. This is a hands-on and strategic role, ideal for a commercially minded finance professional who thrives in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.

Key responsibilities include:

Leading the preparation and management of Opex budgets, forecasts, and variance analysis across multiple business units
Providing insightful financial analysis and commentary to support informed decision-making
Acting as a trusted business partner to cost centre leaders, offering strategic financial advice and challenge where appropriate
Driving continuous improvement in cost control, reporting accuracy, and financial governance
Supporting month-end processes, management reporting, and board-level presentations
Contributing to strategic initiatives and business cases aimed at enhancing operational efficiency
About You
You are a proactive and detail-oriented finance professional with strong analytical and communication skills, capable of influencing senior stakeholders and translating complex financial information into clear business insights. You bring a strong understanding of operational expenditure within large, asset-intensive or service-driven environments.

To be successful, you will have:

A tertiary qualification in Accounting, Finance, or a related discipline
CA or CPA qualification (or equivalent)
Experience in a commercial finance or FP&A role
Demonstrated expertise in Opex management, forecasting, and variance analysis
Proven business partnering experience with operational and non-finance leaders
Advanced Excel; exposure to ERP or BI systems highly regarded
Exceptional communication, stakeholder management, and problem-solving skills
How to Apply If you are a commercially minded Senior Finance Analyst ready to take the next step in your career and contribute to the success of a nationally significant organisation, we’d love to hear from you.

Please click Apply Now to submit your CV or alternatively you can contact Fraser Chapman on fraser.chapman@talentweb.com.au or 0424 155 675.

Ad Text:
Job Description

We are looking for a talented and motivated individual to join our Analytics Team, where you'll play a pivotal role in supporting the Workforce and Innovation division within KPMG's Tax practice. This role is ideal for candidates passionate about data, technology, and problem-solving, with a desire to drive innovation and provide cutting-edge solutions in a collaborative environment.

As an integral member of our team, you will focus on designing, developing, and delivering advanced analytical solutions using automation, data-driven insights, and the latest technologies. Your work will align with KPMG's LEAP strategy, a firm-wide approach focused on Leading Edge Automation and Processes to enhance efficiency, improve client outcomes, and drive innovation in the services we provide.

Your Opportunity

Working with the senior engagement team across multiple clients and projects

Designing, building and optimising client analytical solutions

Work closely with the analytics team in building, optimising and productionising new analytical solutions and models

Build, maintain and deploy private libraries for scalable solutioning

Build and maintain PowerBI dashboards

Growing our portfolio of services by developing innovative solutions, tools or dashboards leveraging client data

Involvement in identifying trends and innovation in data platforms to inform the future development of solutions for our clients and evolving our data analytics platform

Actively adding value by bringing innovation and knowledge into designing and operating solutions as well as sharing knowledge across the team

How are you Extraordinary

A commercial and analytical mindset with complex problem-solving skills

Well-developed written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to influence and present your ideas with impact to clients and other key stakeholders

3+ years of data integration and analytical experience within Workforce, HR and Payroll

3+ years of experience with programming python

Hands on experience in building and deploying analytical solutions for large scale data use cases within Databricks

Extensive and proficient skills in Microsoft Azure (Devops CI/CD pipelines, functions, App services, Containers, SQL server, Databricks)

Attention to detail with strong problem-solving skills

Additional Information

Please note that applications will close on the 20th of November 2025. 

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Title: Senior Lecturer in International Business or Strategic Management
Ad Text:
Classification: Academic Level C 
Salary package: $142,446 - $158,323 per annum plus 17% superannuation  
Terms: Full time, Continuing

Position Description: PD_Senior Lecturer in IB and Strategic Management_2025

Position overview 

The Research School of Management in the ANU College of Business and Economics aims to create and share management knowledge that makes a difference to organisations and society. Nine academics with affiliations to our School are listed among the 2025 Standford/Elsevier Top 2% Scientists.

To continue the current growth trajectory, we are seeking to recruit a Senior Lecturer (Level C) in the field of International Business or Strategic Management. The successful applicant will conduct research of international standing and actively contribute to undergraduate and postgraduate teaching in the School. They will have a strong work ethic, a practical approach, and be passionate about the quality of their work. The successful applicant will join a strong team of academics who publish in top international journals and hold external competitive grants. The School and College provide an excellent research environment, including favourable teaching load and internal research support. 

The position is open to international applicants. The successful applicant must be available to commence work in Canberra (Australia) by mid-2026. The successful applicant will be offered relocation assistance as per ANU Policy. 

We have a strong equal opportunity culture. We encourage all applicants particularly, female, Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander applicants. 

Enquiries: Professor Lin Cui at lin.cui@anu.edu.au.   

College overview 

The Australian National University (ANU) is one of the world’s great universities, ranking 32nd in the 2026 QS World University Rankings. The Research School of Management sits within the ANU College of Business and Economics. The College educates the next generation of business leaders, professional economists and academics. Our graduates have the knowledge and skills to lead organisations, design public policy, and research the big issues of business and economy.

Located in the national capital, we engage deeply with the business and policy communities. Our academics lead public debate on the critical issues of our time through their research, which is both long term and strategic in focus. Our internationally diverse student body is evenly divided between undergraduate and postgraduate study, and we have a large doctoral program. Our alumni are found in the world's leading companies, policy agencies and universities. 

We strongly believe that the way in which we operate is defined by our Values and Behaviours and encourage you to apply if you are looking for a workplace that encourages respect, collegiality and excellence. 

The University actively encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. For more information on employment opportunities, contact our Indigenous Employment Consultant on indigenous.employment@anu.edu.au.

ANU values diversity and inclusion and believes employment opportunities must not be limited by socio-economic background, race, religion or gender. For more information about staff equity at ANU, visit https://services.anu.edu.au/business-units/human-resources-division/equity-and-diversity 

Application information

A statement (3 pages max) addressing each of the selection criteria
A current curriculum vitae (CV) which includes the names and contact details of at least three referees (preferably including a current or previous supervisor). If your CV does not include referees you can provide these online when prompted in the application form.

Team management and training skills including experience/comfort in managing offshore resources. 

Extensive technical skills in catastrophe modelling software such as RMS, Verisk and Impact Forecasting Elements. 

Recognised subject matter expertise and deep interest in natural hazards including cyclones, floods, bushfire, earthquake and storms, catastrophe risk, re/insurance.

We believe this is our moment – what if it was yours too? Your career at QBE — let’s make it happen!

Job Title: Business Profit Growth Analyst for Building Indus
Ad Text:
About Founders Edge

Founders Edge partners with established SME business owners (typically $1M–$10M+ in annual revenue) to help them scale with strategic precision and confidence. Our programs blend board-level strategy, financial modelling, and growth mentorship to help founders achieve extraordinary results — both in business and life.

The Role

We’re looking for a commercially savvy Business Analyst who can turn strategy into numbers — someone who thrives on mapping out how a business can grow over a 10-year horizon using leverage points such as pricing, lead generation, conversion rates, margins, capacity, and team structure.

You’ll work closely with our founder Ryll Burgin-Doyle and our coaching team to create and refine Revenue Resource Maps — dynamic spreadsheets that show business owners exactly how strategic tweaks compound into millions in additional profit and long-term value.

This role requires not just financial skill, but rapport, insight, and curiosity — the ability to engage with SME owners, understand their business model, and translate conversations into clear financial scenarios.

Key Responsibilities

Build and refine 10-year financial growth models (“Revenue Resource Maps”) tailored to each client’s business.



Work with coaches and clients to identify key leverage points for growth (pricing, margins, team utilisation, lead generation, etc.).



Translate qualitative strategy into quantitative outcomes (e.g., revenue targets, profit trajectories, team structure impacts).



Present findings in an engaging, plain-English way — bridging the gap between data and decision-making.



Ensure accuracy, clarity, and alignment with Founders Edge frameworks.



Contribute to ongoing refinement of the Revenue Resource Map templates and systems.



About You

Strong background in financial analysis, business modelling, or commercial advisory — ideally with SME experience (not just corporate).



Comfortable working directly with business owners and senior leaders.



Excellent communication and interpersonal skills — you can make numbers engaging and relevant.



You are excellent at working with Excel/Google Sheets skills; bonus if you can build or improve dynamic models.



Commercial understanding of growth drivers in service-based businesses (particularly building/construction, trade services, or professional services).



Highly organised, detail-oriented, and deadline-driven.



Strategic thinker who understands how to connect operational levers to long-term value creation.



Preferred Background

Experience in SME consulting, business coaching, or fractional CFO/Financial Controller roles.



Prior work in the building, construction, or trade services sector highly regarded.



Exposure to business strategy frameworks and business-growth models a plus.



What You’ll Get

Work directly with a world-class business strategist and her team.



Meaningful, high-impact work helping entrepreneurs grow and thrive.



Flexibility to work remotely, part-time, or full-time (depending on experience).



Competitive compensation with opportunity for ongoing engagement.




You’ll be part of a fast moving, fast growing company that is all about changing lives, transforming businesses and making a difference. We care for our clients deeply and each other. 




Payment:  Generous Hourly Contract Rate Based on Experience. 

Your Next Steps: 




To apply please send your resume and a short video explaining why you would be a great fit for this role through to ja@foundersedgehq.com

Company description:



At Stockland we are a community delivering outcomes that benefit the community at large. We work collaboratively and inclusively, building strong working relationships. Our portfolio is diverse and so are the opportunities for professional and career development. We are committed to providing our people with broad experiences to build a successful career.





Job description:



An exciting opportunity for an Analyst with superior quantitative and financial skills has arisen, based in the Sydney Head Office. Reporting into the Head of Mergers & Acquisitions, this is a key role contributing to Stockland's strategic objectives through analysis and execution of capital markets transactions including mergers, acquisitions, capital partnerships and divestments.




The Opportunity




Your daily responsibilities will include:

Undertake portfolio analysis, valuation and modelling of prospective mergers, acquisitions, capital partnerships and divestments

Assist with preparation of presentations and board papers including coordination with other contributors

Assist in coordinating due diligence with internal and external advisors

Engage and collaborate with key internal customers and stakeholders to build and maintain strong working relationships and drive positive business outcomes

Engage with external advisors to build and maintain strong working relationships and drive positive business outcomes.

Implement stakeholder relationship management initiatives as agreed.

Promote and contribute to a highly collaborative and inclusive team.

Evaluate CR&S and HS&E implications in all capital transaction opportunities.

Implement and participate in corporate initiatives (e.g. volunteering etc).

Act ethically and responsibly with all parties in completing transactions.




About You




University degree qualified - preferably including capital markets or corporate finance with a strong quantitative component (Essential)

Relevant experience in roles in finance or real estate (Desirable)

Advanced analytical, modelling and numerical skills and strong Excel skills

Strong written and verbal communication skills, with high attention to detail




The Stockland Proposition




At Stockland we are a community delivering outcomes that benefit the community at large. We work collaboratively and inclusively, building strong working relationships. Our portfolio is diverse and so are the opportunities for professional and career development. We are committed to providing our people with broad experiences to build a successful career.




Stockland has a strong commitment to achieving the best outcomes through an inclusive and collaborative culture. Our customers come from diverse backgrounds and we want our teams to reflect this.




We offer competitive remuneration and benefits. Benefits include free to access or subsidised lifestyle, health, well-being and financial services products.




Due to the permanent nature of this role, we can only accept applications from Australian Citizens, Permanent Residents or Open Work Visa holders with more than 12 months validity from their role start date.




Apply today - Stockland - it's your place.




Agencies should note that unsolicited resumes will not be accepted for this position and Stockland will not pay any fees related to resumes that are submitted directly to hiring managers and not through our approved process. Where appropriate, the Careers @ Stockland Team will work with our preferred panel of agencies to source candidates for roles. Please submit any queries relating to the approved process of submitting candidate resumes or Stockland's preferred agency panel to careers@stockland.com.au

Ad Text:
Are you an experienced finance leader ready to drive corporate management accounting and performance reporting across Queensland Health? Step into the role of Director, Analysis in Finance Branch and drive expert insights, lead a high-performing team, and champion greater transparency. Benefit from flexible work arrangements, professional growth opportunities, and the chance to make a meaningful impact.

What you'll do

Co-ordinate and complete effective executive reporting, including identifing significant variations and trends across Queensland Health.
Provide high quality advice, information and guidance to Executive Management, HHSs and Divisions, particularly in relation to financial analysis and management.
Proactively identify business improvement opportunities and recommend strategies to realise the benefits.
Ensure that systems are established and maintained to provide budget transparency and forecasting integrity.
Lead and promote a professional and responsive team to meet the information and financial management advice needs of health services.

About you

We are searching for someone with:

Accounting qualifications and membership of a recognised professional accounting body.
Demonstrated ability to provide effective leadership and management at a senior level within a service delivery organisation involving multi-disciplinary programs and diverse work units.
High-level knowledge of financial management legislation relevant to Queensland Health.
Highly developed communication and interpersonal competence, including the capacity to negotiate, resolve conflict and positively influence and motivate others in a significant environment of reform and change.
Well-developed skills, including high level ability in the areas of planning, managing resources, budget preparation and management, project management, objective setting and monitoring, coaching and performance feedback and management.
Proven issue identification, analytical and research skills, problem solving skills and a demonstrated ability to develop innovative, sensitive and practical solutions and provide strategic advice to complex issues.
Understanding of the financial pressures and constraints that impact service delivery and the capacity to recommend courses of action which achieve optimal outcomes within those constraints.

Why work with us?

Work alongside passionate professionals in a supportive and inclusive environment that values people and prioritises employee success and wellbeing. This includes

Competitive salaries

12.75% superannuation
17.5% leave loading

Employee wellbeing

38 hour full time work week
Access to 24/7 confidential employee support providers and counsellors including for immediate family members
Additional flexibility to support your work life balance including access to generous leave entitlements, such as purchased leave, domestic violence leave, reproductive health leave, cultural leave, study and examination leave.

Professional development

Career progression with more than 300 diverse career pathways and career support to take you further!
Access to a variety of programs and initiatives to support training and career growth.
Grow your skills through hands-on experience and access to internal training opportunities and additional financial and leave benefits for approved external training and development.

Our commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion 

At Queensland Health, our work environment is inclusive and supportive, and we value our employees. We are an equal opportunity employer and encourage applications from people of all cultures, abilities and backgrounds.

Our commitment to cultural safety, equity, diversity and inclusion means we understand some people may need changes to the recruitment process. If you need support during the recruitment process, such as meeting with the panel virtually instead of in person, please reach out to the hiring manager. We value diverse candidates and your need for adjustments will not affect our hiring decisions. 

Ready to apply?

For further information on how to apply please review the attached Role Description.

Applications will remain current for a period of up to 12 months and may be considered for other vacancies which may include an alternative employment basis such as temporary, full time or part time.
